    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> crushed garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>to the dish with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong>, your<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>mirin</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and 3/4 of your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), then, give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with a lid and put it in the oven for 25 min or until the aubergine wedges are tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
