    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> then chop it into large, bite-sized pieces – this is your<strong> smashed cucumber</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong>, the <strong>remaining gochujang paste</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), <strong>refreshed edamame beans </strong>and <strong>smashed cucumber </strong>to a bowl and mix everything together – this is your<strong> gochujang cucumber & edamame salad</strong></p>",
